data.meta_description:
63 likes, 5 comments - mrpaulfeinstein on July 21, 2021: "Tulum is littered with contradictions. Spiritual yet hedonistic. Artsy but lousy with influencers. Beautiful but the beach is covered with rotting seaweed.
.
This brilliant sculpture is by artist @danielpopper and is called Ven a la Luz (come into the light) which epitomizes Tulum. Meant as a symbol of connecting humans and nature yet packed with lines of people waiting for a pic who couldnâ€™t care less about its meaning.
.
Support Artists and Go Travel!".
